node:018f8366 a kg:Function ;
    rdfs:label "sign_rsa_sha1" ;
    kg:branches 0 ;
    kg:calls node:0062a6a0 ;
    kg:depends_on node:2a9fac43 ;
    kg:docstring """**RSA-SHA1**

    Per `section 3.4.3`_ of the spec.

    The "RSA-SHA1" signature method uses the RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5 signature
    algorithm as defined in `RFC3447, Section 8.2`_ (also known as
    PKCS#1), using SHA-1 as the hash function for EMSA-PKCS1-v1_5.  To
    use this method, the client MUST have established client credentials
    with the server that included its RSA public key (in a manner that is
    beyond the scope of this specification).

    NOTE: this method requires the python-rsa library.

    .. _`section 3.4.3`: http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5849#section-3.4.3
    .. _`RFC3447, Section 8.2`: http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3447#section-8.2""" ;
    kg:filepath "requests/packages/oauthlib/oauth1/rfc5849/signature.py" ;
    kg:isAsync false ;
    kg:lineno 441 ;
    kg:param [ kg:paramName "rsa_private_key" ],
        [ kg:paramName "base_string" ] ;
    kg:repo "psf/requests" .

